      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW LASSIE (3) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing sixth (24.00) in a Grade 5 at Horsham. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Looks the one to beat on her best form. OPAL WHISPER (1) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 1.75 lengths second (28.81) over 500m at Bendigo. Hard to beat again. IVORY MIHARA (6) finds it hard to win. Better run when finding the frame last time though, finishing third (30.74) at this track. Expected to feature again. BIT OF POTASH (7) hit the frame latest (26.47) when second at Geelong in a Rank Limit - Grade 5. Has already won out of this draw.",
